## Issue 5: mediate() is not compatible with svyolr() models

With this partial success, we checked to see if we could also run this latest mediation on the weighted data.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
model_m_5 <- survey::svyolr(
  formula = informal_support_ordinal ~ race,
  design = dat_weights
)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-error}
```
Error in optim(s0, fmin, gmin, method = "BFGS", ...): initial value in 'vmmin' is not finite
```
:::
:::


This throws an error, which [this StackOverflow post](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/28916377/r-error-with-polr-initial-value-in-vmmin-is-not-finite?rq=2) can help us solve. We can help the function by providing plausible start values for the coefficients and the intercepts/thresholds. We have one coefficient and three thresholds (from 0 to 1, from 1 to 2, and from 2 to 3), and we know they should be relatively close to zero as well as that the thresholds should be in ascending order. With the syntax `start = c(coefficients, thresholds)` we can make it work:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
model_m_5 <- survey::svyolr(
  formula = informal_support_ordinal ~ race,
  design = dat_weights,
  start = c(0, -1, 0, 1)
)

summary(model_m_5)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
